        <num>CC 1942</num>
        <heading>1942.  Acceptance by silence</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1942.  Acceptance by silence
When, because of special circumstances, the offeree's silence leads the offeror reasonably to believe that a contract has been formed, the offer is deemed accepted.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109191</p>
